>>>	secretending_omenredeemed
>event_type	ending
>ending_type	secretending
>layout	none
	narrator		You go check on Omen. These last few days have been quite intense for them!
>layout	solo	omen
	player	default	Omen, hi! How are you doing?
	omen	default	Hey, %CURRENTPLAYERNAME%.	O_greetings4
	omen	confident	I'm... I'm actually doing quite well.
	player	default	Oh, really?
	omen	evil	Yeah. Dumb Liam wasn't wrong: facing my past and trying to amend my errors has felt sort of liberating.
	player	default	That's so nice to hear!
	player	default	Did you hear from the Slayers?
	omen	default	Actually, I did. They contacted me earlier today and we had a meeting.
	omen	default	The Coven apparently vouched for me, so the Slayers have said I might be helpful if I joined them on some of their missions.
	player	default	Great!
	omen	default	Also, it seems they have recently learned of a rogue Slayer who has been acting on their own for the past few years.	Oex_default
	omen	unimpressed	Being a free agent goes against the code of the Slayers, so they are hesitant about how to act on it.
	omen	confident	But they mentioned that perhaps I could be the one to make contact, since I know the importance of the Slayer ways and have been a rogue Slayer myself.
	player	default	I was actually meaning to ask... and don't answer if you don't want to... but how come you went rogue?
	omen	default	Nah, it's okay.
	omen	bummed	I... I grew impatient.	Oex_bummed
	omen	default	The Slayers' ways require a lot of trust in the group, and A LOT of patience.	
	omen	default	Sometimes you must accept that your life's work will be but a tiny cog in the machine that is the Slayers' mission.
	omen	bummed	Results may only be perceived after several generations.
	omen	default	And so, once in a while, a Slayer (often a gifted one) will believe that they are different, that they can get things done faster.
	omen	bummed	I was one of them: I believed I could become the Spear of Monsterkind myself.
	omen	confident	But if the ways of the Slayers are to be believed, no one is meant to become that themselves. The Spear of Monsterkind is all of us, together.
	player	default	I see.
	omen	unimpressed	To fulfill that ambition you must attain power... and power tends to corrupt.
	omen	bummed	I thought I was different, and yet I ended up the same way as almost all rogue Slayers have.
	player	default	No, Omen, you didn't end like the other rogue Slayers... because your story is not done.
	player	default	You've made mistakes, but I've seen you making an effort to change.
	player	default	So, I could be mistaken, but I choose to believe you are an omen of good things to come.
	omen	default	%CURRENTPLAYERNAME%...
	omen	confident	Thank you.	Oex_confident
>layout	none
	narrator		You and Omen spend some time together. They seem to be... at peace.
>secretending_picture
>special_command	playeventnamesfxover
	narrator		They open themself up to you and tell you some of their war stories from back when they were a Slayer.	O_ending_redeemed1
	narrator		And soon, they make new ones too.
	narrator		Omen proves themself to be a valuable asset to the Slayers, helping to slowly but steadily move the needle in favor of the forces of good.
	narrator		And what's most important: they stick to the Redemption Arc Program, even helping others in their process.
	narrator		This also becomes their own way of showing Liam how grateful they are, without the need to openly admit that he was right.
	narrator		And you're there by their side, happy to bear witness to their growth.

